# NestJS Conventions

## Module Structure

One feature per module under `src/<feature>/`:

```
posts/
├── posts.module.ts
├── posts.controller.ts
├── posts.service.ts
├── dto/
│   ├── create-post.dto.ts
│   └── update-post.dto.ts
└── entities/
    └── post.entity.ts
```

## Patterns

- Use `@nestjs/swagger` decorators on every controller endpoint and DTO field.
- Validate input with `class-validator` + `ValidationPipe` (global).
- Return consistent response shape:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
return { data: post, message: 'Post created' };

// ❌ BAD — raw entity without wrapper
return post;
```

- Use **TypeORM** repositories via `@InjectRepository()`; avoid raw SQL unless necessary.
- Run schema changes via TypeORM migrations (`npm run migration:generate`, `migration:run`).
- Map entities to response DTOs — never expose internal fields (passwords, tokens).

## Authentication (JWT + Passport)

- Auth module: `src/auth/` with `JwtStrategy`, `JwtAuthGuard`, `AuthService`.
- Issue JWT on login/register; store `JWT_SECRET` and `JWT_EXPIRES_IN` in env.
- Protected routes: `@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard)` + `@ApiBearerAuth()`.
- Public routes must be explicitly marked (no guard).
- Access current user via `@Request() req` → `req.user` (set by JwtStrategy).

```typescript
@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard)
@ApiBearerAuth()
@Get('drafts')
findMyDrafts(@Request() req) {
  return this.draftsService.findByAuthor(req.user.id);
}
```

## Naming

- Files: kebab-case (`create-post.dto.ts`)
- Classes: PascalCase (`CreatePostDto`, `PostsService`)
- Endpoints: plural nouns (`/posts`, `/posts/:id`)
- HTTP verbs: GET (read), POST (create), PATCH (partial update), DELETE (remove)

## Error Handling

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
throw new NotFoundException(`Post with id ${id} not found`);

// ❌ BAD
throw new Error('not found');
```

## Register New Modules

Always import feature modules in `app.module.ts`.
